Defendant Andra D Bond in court with attorney Darryl Everett Smith.  Defendant Andra D Bond in custody.  
Kimberly Dorice Schoepp appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Matter before the Court for Sentencing.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by the state, defense, and defendant. 
 
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction, STRAIGHT TIME with credit for 3 days.  

The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 1 YEAR with the following conditions.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
*Cooperate with any counseling/programming deemed appropriated by agent;
*Absolute sobriety with random urine screens;
*Continue participation at River's Shore Clinic and Milwaukee Achiever;
*Obtain/maintain employment after programming complete;
*Provide DNA sample- pay surcharge;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs by the end of probation period- any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment;

The Court instructs defense counsel to advise the defendant of appeal rights. 
Filed;
